            <h3>How to Apply for a Business Major</h3>
            <p>Applying to the College of Business Administration is easy and straightforward—if you meet all of the requirements outlined below, your admission is guaranteed!</p>
            <p>Because the University does not guarantee acceptance to majors; College of Business students who plan to pursue a business degree are accepted to the college as preliminary business students, also known as “business pending” students.  Students seeking to declare and complete a major as part of the College of Business must meet the following requirements to qualify:</p>
            <p>Completion of UCF’s General Education Program, including the Gordon Rule Requirements with a minimum overall GPA of 2.0; or an AA degree awarded from a Florida public institution (including Community College, State College, and University) with a minimum overall GPA of 2.0.</p>
            
        </div>
