            <h3>Prerequisite Business Course Requirements</h3>
            <p>You must complete ALL prerequisite courses with a minimum of a 2.0 GPA and “C” or better in each class before you can be admitted to the College of Business.</p>

            <ul>
                <li>ACG 2021 Introduction to Financial Accounting</li>
                <li>ACG 2071 Introduction to Managerial Accounting</li>
                <li>ECO 2013 Principles of Macroeconomics</li>
                <li>ECO 2023 Principles of Microeconomics</li>
                <li>CGS 2100 Fundamentals of Computers in Business</li>
                <li>ECO 3401 Quantitative Business Tools <small>- OR -</small></li>
                <li>STA 2023 and MAC 2233	Introduction to Statistics  and Survey of Calculus</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Pre Business Course Requirements</h3>

            <h4>Transfer Students</h4>
            <p>All newly admitted students are required to attend a mandatory orientation session. Students receive notification and documentation about signing up for the UCF Orientation Program once they are admitted to the university. At orientation, students meet with representatives from Undergraduate Student Services and are provided information (i.e., deadlines, policies and procedures) regarding UCF and the College of Business Administration. Advisors discuss major requirements and assist in creating a class schedule for the incoming semester.</p>

